40:59.960 --> 41:04.480
Bobby Kennedy had just been assassinated. It was June 68. It was a big blow to me. I thought

41:04.480 --> 41:08.980
Bobby was going to be our way of getting out of Vietnam, the end of some of the racial stuff that

41:08.980 --> 41:15.520
was going on. So this was like a major blow. Another Kennedy assassinated, right? My friend

41:15.520 --> 41:20.140
had different ideas. To him, this was an opportunity. He says, they're going to have the funeral in New

41:20.140 --> 41:26.180
York City at St. Patrick's Cathedral. We know the people at St. Patrick's. Why don't we just go down

41:26.180 --> 41:33.160
there during the funeral and just gatecrash it, you know? And I said, they're going to have the

41:33.160 --> 41:38.160
tightest security New York has ever known, if not the country. Another Kennedy assassinated,

41:38.520 --> 41:43.780
and the president's going to be there? And the senators and the congressmen and the cabinet and

41:43.780 --> 41:48.080
God knows who else, they're all going to be in this room? I don't think so. He says, no, let's just try it.

41:48.080 --> 41:54.260
So we got on the subway the night before and we go down and we talked to some guy in there and,

41:54.360 --> 42:00.720
you know, we're in our full regalia and he says, oh, okay. Um, I don't know. Uh, you're not on the

42:00.720 --> 42:04.500
list, but, you know, come by and then if we can get you in, we'll get you in something like that.

42:04.980 --> 42:10.440
So we say, okay, cool. We're two 17 year olds. Does this make any freaking sense at all?

42:10.740 --> 42:11.620
No, it doesn't.

42:11.680 --> 42:11.980
At all.

42:12.120 --> 42:12.400
Yeah.

42:12.400 --> 42:19.260
No. So they say, okay. So we say, fine, we're doing it. Right. So we go into the church proper.

42:19.400 --> 42:25.200
The casket is already there. Bobby is in St. Patrick's Saturday night. So we go up to it and,

42:25.240 --> 42:30.380
you know, do appropriately religious things. And in the pew, the only people in the church at the

42:30.380 --> 42:37.860
time is Rose Kennedy and, uh, uh, Jackie Onassis. So they're there praying and we're looking at them

42:37.860 --> 42:40.280
and, you know, and they're looking at us like, who are all these people? Right.

42:40.480 --> 42:40.720
Whoa.

42:40.720 --> 42:47.340
So we do this thing and we just quietly leave. So the next day, Sunday, uh, my friend says,

42:47.460 --> 42:52.660
we're going to do this. Right. I said, we can give it a shot. You know, we rent a limo

42:52.660 --> 43:02.480
and we rent this limo and we take it from the Bronx to St. Patrick's. It's really weird what you can get

43:02.480 --> 43:07.120
away with in a limo. Right. The limo pulls up to the side entrance of the church where all the

43:07.120 --> 43:13.460
celebrities are getting out and we're in the limo. So we must belong. Right. The driver opens up the

43:13.460 --> 43:19.280
door. We get out and all this stuff that we're wearing. Um, and the secret service runs right up

43:19.280 --> 43:26.160
to us. And we had made a decision, my friend and I, that he would not speak because he's like a foreign

43:26.160 --> 43:30.860
speaking person. And I would do all the talking because I'm a fast talker, as you can possibly

43:30.860 --> 43:35.080
realize now, but I had to do it in a foreign accent. Right. Because we had to be foreign

43:35.080 --> 43:40.060
dignitaries. So the secret service agent walks up to us and he says, Russian Orthodox representatives.

43:40.060 --> 43:47.600
And I say, no, Slavonic Orthodox representatives. And he says, oh, okay, follow me. And he leads us

43:47.600 --> 43:54.440
into the church, leads us into the sanctuary where all the other religious dignitaries are sitting

43:54.440 --> 43:58.700
on the other side of the communion rail. If you're Catholics, any of you listening, you know,

43:58.760 --> 44:02.720
you don't go on the other side of the communion rail, unless you're a priest or an altar boy or

44:02.720 --> 44:07.760
something. You have some particular religious sacerdotal reason to be there. But we're, we're stuck

44:07.760 --> 44:12.540
right in the, right in the front. Right. My friend on one side and me on the other, we're just staring

44:12.540 --> 44:17.680
at each other. We're in there and all these bishops and clergy and other Orthodox bishops are

44:17.680 --> 44:23.300
there. So it's freaking us out. Right. But we're brassing it out. We think, well, we're here, you know,

44:23.320 --> 44:29.900
no one's going to believe this story. And if I had been anybody else, if I had been a different

44:29.900 --> 44:34.900
person, I could have walked in there with a device. You know what I mean? I would have taken out

44:34.900 --> 44:41.440
the American leadership was in that room, not just the religious leadership. It's an incredible

44:41.440 --> 44:47.720
failure of security that this was allowed to happen. I mean, it's incredibly wrong. And yet

44:47.720 --> 44:52.440
we just brass it out like we belong there. So we did do that. You know, we, we were there for the

44:52.440 --> 44:57.680
whole service. Um, and then because we're the last ones in, we were the first ones out. So we were

44:57.680 --> 45:03.420
supposed to lead the procession out of the cathedral, lead it. No one knew who the hell we were.

45:03.420 --> 45:08.920
The TV cameras are pointing at us. The Klieg lights are all over us. No one knows who to,

45:09.000 --> 45:09.880
how to identify us.

45:09.920 --> 45:13.780
So there's probably video of you leading a funeral procession for Bobby Kennedy.

45:13.780 --> 45:19.680
I've been looking at this for it for a long time. There's a very bad, very blurry video.

45:19.820 --> 45:20.440
That's wild.

45:20.640 --> 45:23.380
You would think there would be some perfect video of that, but there isn't.

45:23.380 --> 45:24.720
That's a Forrest Gump moment.

45:24.960 --> 45:25.420
If I've ever.

45:25.580 --> 45:25.920
Absolutely.

45:26.220 --> 45:27.180
A zeleg moment.

45:27.280 --> 45:27.720
Yeah, zeleg.

45:27.840 --> 45:28.160
Wild.

45:28.160 --> 45:35.100
Yeah. But there is. And I just got, uh, just a couple of days ago, a still that somebody got

45:35.100 --> 45:41.340
of the procession and the two of us are there. So we, I know now, you know, this tangible evidence

45:41.340 --> 45:45.960
that exists, it's blurry, but it's us. I mean, you could look and you can see these guys don't

45:45.960 --> 45:50.980
belong where they are. So we led the procession out. It's another story. But how great was that?

45:51.020 --> 45:56.120
Because I had Andy Williams behind me singing the battle hymn of the Republic. I had Leonard

45:56.120 --> 46:01.160
Bernstein conducting the hallelujah chorus from the, from Handel's Messiah, right? As

46:01.160 --> 46:05.120
the door is open on Rockefeller Center and Atlas holding up the world. And this is in

46:05.120 --> 46:10.320
June 68. I'm supposed to graduate high school that month. Right. And it's like, who needs

46:10.320 --> 46:14.800
graduation, man? This is cool. This is it. You know, but we also know we're in deep shit.

46:14.800 --> 46:20.600
If somebody stops us, you know, it's all over. So we know how to get out of the church.

46:21.020 --> 46:25.440
There's an underground kind of a passageway. It's not really that secret, but unless you know,

46:25.440 --> 46:29.960
you know, you won't know it. So we decided to go out that way. And as we're going out that way,

46:30.020 --> 46:34.060
of course, we run into Rose Kennedy and Jackie again, who were also trying to go out that same

46:34.060 --> 46:38.400
way. So we get out, but we take the subway back. We didn't keep the limo too expensive.

46:39.420 --> 46:45.520
And then we got back to the Bronx and went back to school the next day, you know, with teachers and

46:45.520 --> 46:54.280
students looking at us and, you know, saying, nah, can't be right. So we managed this. But the thing

46:54.280 --> 46:59.340
is, the reason I'm telling you this story is because on our way out, we bump into guys from

46:59.340 --> 47:01.200
the American Orthodox Catholic Church.

47:01.380 --> 47:02.160
The intelligence front.

47:02.360 --> 47:05.880
The intelligence front. They're outside. They couldn't get in. We did.

47:05.980 --> 47:06.540
That's wild.

47:06.640 --> 47:07.100
They couldn't.

47:07.280 --> 47:07.520
Yeah.

47:07.660 --> 47:12.820
They're handing us this sort of brochure. They're saying, come and see us. Right. And so we're looking

47:12.820 --> 47:16.020
at each other. And we said, why not? We never heard of this place. It's near the Bronx Zoo,

47:16.260 --> 47:20.760
if that means anything. So let's go and take a look. And we took a look and we wound up joining,

47:21.200 --> 47:27.120
right? Because we needed, we were two 17-year-olds, you know, my friend turned 18 that month. So we

47:27.120 --> 47:30.360
needed to know that we're going to get out of the selective service thing, out of the draft.

47:30.940 --> 47:42.160
And so one thing led to another and we did. But there was a quid pro quo for this. So I turned

47:42.160 --> 47:46.820
18 at a different time than my friend did. So he got his clearance before I did. So I

47:46.820 --> 47:52.020
was brought to the selective service board, the headquarters in New York City, to talk

47:52.020 --> 47:58.100
to the head of selective service. He's a really strange guy. I'll never forget him. He wore

47:58.100 --> 48:02.540
these, you know, elbow patches, tweet jacket kind of guy, looking like an intelligence guy,

48:02.540 --> 48:08.400
looking like Alan Dulles kind of, you know. And he said, okay, no problem. You know, we're

48:08.400 --> 48:11.820
going to give you the thing. Unless you want to be a chaplain in Vietnam, we can arrange

48:11.820 --> 48:18.280
that making a little joke. Very funny. He says, this is the thing though. He says, the

48:18.280 --> 48:24.980
Russians have been moving agents into the United States through the Orthodox churches. Keep

48:24.980 --> 48:31.560
an eye out. You let us know when you see one coming through because you know who's real

48:31.560 --> 48:35.680
and who isn't, right? You keep an eye out and just let us know. That's all. And you're

48:35.680 --> 48:36.120
cool.

48:38.240 --> 48:41.140
So they were trying to basically operationalize you somewhat.

48:41.140 --> 48:45.780
Well, the church itself, as I found out later, I found out years and years later. I mean,

48:45.800 --> 48:51.280
I always suspected because I know I saw weird shit going on in that church from the beginning. But

48:51.280 --> 48:56.960
I found out years later, going through Jim Garrison's files, he had finally, they finally

48:56.960 --> 49:02.120
released his correspondence. And when I got to his correspondence and I finally saw it,

49:02.160 --> 49:05.780
I found church stationery that I had typed on back in the day.

49:05.900 --> 49:06.300
Wild.

49:06.760 --> 49:12.340
Where the leader of the church, a guy called Propheta, was writing letters to Jim Garrison

49:12.340 --> 49:17.720
saying, when you're finished with Jack Martin, can you send him back to us? Right? So it's

49:17.720 --> 49:19.420
there. It's in print. It's in the files.

49:19.420 --> 49:25.440
Well, also a wild synchronicity that you end up researching the JFK assassination. And you had

49:25.440 --> 49:30.480
been a part of this American Orthodox Catholic church that was this intelligence front, which

49:30.480 --> 49:35.620
had something to do with the JFK assassination. That is a time loop if I've ever seen one.

49:35.800 --> 49:37.100
It doesn't make any freaking sense.

49:37.200 --> 49:38.220
It doesn't make any sense.

49:38.480 --> 49:40.940
I was 17. How the hell did we wind up in that position?

49:43.040 --> 49:49.380
What's up, guys? One of today's sponsors is us, American Alchemy. We just launched

49:49.380 --> 49:54.280
what I think is maybe the coolest merch line in the world. When you're wearing it, it's

49:54.280 --> 49:58.280
not like you're shilling me or the channel. They're just really epic and I think they look

49:58.280 --> 50:04.260
good. We have a couple of amazing designs for you. We have our cowboy UFO tee. Pretty epic.

50:04.460 --> 50:10.180
You see there's a rancher. He's witnessing a UFO. A little cow is getting abducted by the

50:10.180 --> 50:15.660
UFO in the background. And then you know that I love mid-century history, specifically spooky

50:15.660 --> 50:24.180
science, atomic era stuff. And so we have our atomic age tee here. Pretty cool vibe.

50:24.560 --> 50:30.800
You got a robot serving this guy. A little martini and then a UFO off to the side.

50:31.080 --> 50:40.540
Go to AmericanAlchemyMerch.com. AmericanAlchemy. M-E-R-C-H.com to check out all of this amazing

50:40.540 --> 50:46.360
new apparel. The cowboy tee that I'm wearing is 100% cotton, super relaxed fit. We went for quality

50:46.360 --> 50:54.440
on these. So check them out. So they say when you're getting briefed, like, hey, just look out

50:54.440 --> 51:01.580
for Russian spies. How much more involvement do you have with the church itself? And do you see them

51:01.580 --> 51:06.400
do anything else that's kind of suspicious or interesting on the intelligence front?

51:06.400 --> 51:13.160
When we were researching for our cover story as Orthodox priests, we had a lot of friends

51:13.160 --> 51:20.100
in two different Orthodox churches. One was the Russian Orthodox Church outside Russia. This is

51:20.100 --> 51:27.200
important because it shows up again in New Orleans. Because all those Russians around Lee Oswald and

51:27.200 --> 51:33.560
Marina, all the people he was being introduced to, okay, were members of the Russian Orthodox Church

51:33.560 --> 51:40.120
outside Russia. These were the Russian Orthodox who were anti-communist. They fled Moscow during the

51:40.120 --> 51:47.320
revolution, the Russian Revolution in 1917. They fled to Paris first, and then they opened up this

51:47.320 --> 51:52.400
operation in New York. So these are Romanovs, right? And they brought all their treasure with them,

51:52.420 --> 51:56.500
and they brought a lot of priests and bishops and stuff, and they established this church on the

51:56.500 --> 52:01.880
Upper East Side in Manhattan on Park Avenue and 93rd Street. And we would go in there all the time,

52:01.880 --> 52:07.420
right? This was like Dr. Zhivago territory. It was pure Russia. I mean, you were in Russia when you're

52:07.420 --> 52:12.180
on those premises, right? So there was a high school there. We befriended the principal of the high

52:12.180 --> 52:19.020
school. So we would know a lot of background stuff of what was going on until the other Russians found

52:19.020 --> 52:25.140
out that he was talking to us, in which case they pushed him down an elevator shaft and broke his legs.

52:25.140 --> 52:31.480
We visited him in the hospital, and he says, don't come back again. That was Brother Victor,

52:31.680 --> 52:37.720
another whole story. The other church was the one on 97th Street and 5th, and that was the Russian

52:37.720 --> 52:43.620
church that owed allegiance to Moscow. That's the one they were running agents through. We would go

52:43.620 --> 52:46.960
there once in a while just to hang out and watch them, because they had a whole different way of

52:46.960 --> 52:51.000
doing the liturgy. It was kind of a different setup. And we would just sit there and watch them,

52:51.000 --> 52:57.740
and we would know when a young priest showed up from the old country. And there's one particular

52:57.740 --> 53:06.780
thing you're taught during ordination. That's a kind of a secret prayer that is responsible for

53:06.780 --> 53:10.780
changing the bread and wine into the body and blood, right? Which is the whole transubstantiation

53:10.780 --> 53:15.560
thing that we learned about in Catholic school. Well, in the Orthodox Church, it's almost the same,

53:15.560 --> 53:21.600
kind of similar. But there's a prayer and a gesture that you do to make this change official,

53:21.860 --> 53:28.720
to call down the forces to make this happen. They don't know it, because they didn't go through

53:28.720 --> 53:35.180
the actual real training. They went through training to be spies, and they got enough training to pass as

53:35.180 --> 53:41.420
Orthodox priests, but they didn't get everything quite often. Sometimes the people in Moscow cleverly

53:41.420 --> 53:47.240
kept that back a little bit. And that was a signal to the guys back in the States or abroad, wherever,

53:47.460 --> 53:52.760
that the person they were sending over was not to be trusted, right? He was KGB. So you had priests

53:52.760 --> 53:58.200
who were KGB. Now, if you ever watched, there was an American television series called The Americans.

53:59.340 --> 54:04.880
It was about a husband and wife, deep sleeper agents in the United States during that time.

54:04.880 --> 54:11.500
The very last season, for those of you who can go back and take a look, featured finally,

54:11.580 --> 54:15.400
because I watched that thing from beginning to end waiting for this, the final season showed

54:15.400 --> 54:22.240
the priests who were KGB agents operating as priests. And they were running operations in New York.

54:22.660 --> 54:28.180
And so they finally talked about it. But for us, that was a big deal. And that basically kept me out

54:28.180 --> 54:34.140
of Vietnam also, right? So this was an important aspect of all of this, was the fact that all of

54:34.140 --> 54:39.540
this was going on. Now, this is all happening in 1968, right? I'm still 18. By that time,

54:39.560 --> 54:44.800
I'm 18 years old. So now, I mean, I'm in the middle of all of this stuff. But I don't know

54:44.800 --> 54:49.260
what's related to the Kennedy assassination at all. I have no clue. But I know there's intelligence

54:49.260 --> 54:53.880
operations going on. I know this guy is running ops because the only people who ever showed up

54:53.880 --> 54:59.240
were FBI, CIA types, right? And he bragged about it, the bishop who ran the church,

54:59.240 --> 55:08.260
profeta. He was very proud of the fact. And he constantly said that his people were vetted by

55:08.260 --> 55:13.500
J. Edgar Hoover himself. That's how the vetting was going on. That's why he called people back

55:13.500 --> 55:18.980
to have them vetted. Hoover himself would approve or disapprove his selection of priests and bishops.

55:18.980 --> 55:26.280
So this was obviously for what reason, right? It had to be for an intelligence operation. So we had

55:26.280 --> 55:30.480
strange guys coming in from all over the world to become bishops. People didn't even know how to

55:30.480 --> 55:34.660
genuflect or make the sign of the cross, right? And we're making these guys bishops, giving them

55:34.660 --> 55:39.920
papers and sending them back, photographing the ritual so it looks legit. So this was happening all

55:39.920 --> 55:45.840
the time. So we had guys from Italy at one point. So the Italian consulate sent people to observe

55:45.840 --> 55:51.500
this one guy becoming a bishop and we're sending him back. But the weirdest one was during the Biafra

55:51.500 --> 55:58.240
crisis in Nigeria. Also in the 60s, there was a civil war going on in Nigeria. So you had the

55:58.240 --> 56:06.080
Biafrans who were like the Christian element fighting against a Muslim group in Nigeria. So they were

56:06.080 --> 56:14.700
looking for independence from Nigeria. So the Nigerians sent us this guy. I'll never forget him because I

56:14.700 --> 56:20.220
had to go to the airport to pick him up. His name was the Holy Prophet Alouya. That was his name.

56:20.660 --> 56:28.040
H.P. Alouya. Holy Prophet H.P. I picked him up at the airport in, excuse me, in all kinds of

56:28.040 --> 56:33.860
African garb, right? So as he would be as an African. So I pick him up at the airport. We take the

56:35.360 --> 56:42.540
limo, I guess, back to the Bronx. And he's going on about, you know, how happy he is and all the rest of

56:42.540 --> 56:48.460
it to be, you know, a member of this organization. And we consecrate him a bishop. He's now Bishop

56:48.460 --> 56:54.340
Holy Prophet Alouya. And the Nigerian embassy is there. No, the Nigerian consulate, rather, in New York

56:54.340 --> 57:02.140
is there. It's the Nigerian side, not the Biafran side, not the Christian side. It's the other side, the

57:02.140 --> 57:08.420
nationalist side, the federal side, that won him as a bishop, as a Christian bishop, to convince other

57:08.420 --> 57:15.380
Nigerians in the Christian side to stay with Nigeria as against Biafra. This was a ploy in the Civil War.

57:15.380 --> 57:19.940
The Civil War was raging when we did this. And we put him back on the plane the next day. He goes

57:19.940 --> 57:23.800
back to Nigeria. God knows what happened to him after that. We don't know. Never heard from him

57:23.800 --> 57:30.120
again. This is fascinating. And it's just touching off a whole life for you of catching the attention

57:30.120 --> 57:36.440
of intelligence agencies. By accident. By accident. Through pure serendipity. And I want to make that

57:36.440 --> 57:41.780
clear to any conspiratorial audience members, because I think that is emblematic, actually, of your life is

57:41.780 --> 57:50.260
it seems like you kind of try to, you seek kind of sacred truth. And I think at times that sacred

57:50.260 --> 57:55.980
truth is, you know, incidental to knowledge that might be held by, you know, government organizations,

57:55.980 --> 58:03.820
and then they get very interested in you. You started this story off by saying, first rule of

58:03.820 --> 58:09.520
Fight Club. And then you also said that this story was sort of indicative for you of just how

58:09.520 --> 58:16.440
trippy reality is, how there's something else going on. Why is that for you? And why, how do you think

58:16.440 --> 58:18.340
the Fight Club analogy relates to this?

58:18.340 --> 58:21.280
Yeah, good question, because I'm glad you picked up on that.

58:24.400 --> 58:30.520
I barely graduated high school. I came from a kind of a broken home situation. So there's a lot of

58:30.520 --> 58:36.280
weirdness in my family. We had traveled around a lot here and there. Strange things happened to us.

58:36.400 --> 58:43.060
And for a while, in 1965, 66, I was fascinated with occultism in general, at least what we knew of it

58:43.060 --> 58:49.500
at the time, which was not much. And so Ouija board stuff, seances, that kind of thing. So I was like

58:49.500 --> 58:56.820
totally into it. And it was a source of paranormal phenomenon. We actually had paranormal phenomenon.

58:56.820 --> 59:00.620
We were kids. I was 15 years old. I had a brother and sister who were younger.

59:01.020 --> 59:01.560
What would happen?

59:02.280 --> 59:06.480
You know, table levitation, that kind of the table rising, table tapping phenomenon that the

59:06.480 --> 59:08.720
Victorians were so proud of.

59:08.840 --> 59:09.080
Yeah.

59:09.400 --> 59:13.280
So we had that. We had tables rising in the air, slamming down. We had knocks on the table,

59:13.480 --> 59:19.360
all of that stuff. And I'm going to high school in the Bronx, you know, taking science classes.

59:19.360 --> 59:24.200
And I know that I can't talk about this to anybody, right? Because this is against the,

59:24.360 --> 59:30.120
you know, they would tell me I was crazy or imagining it and, you know, questioning my sanity

59:30.120 --> 59:35.340
or whatever. And, but I know what I saw, right? So these things would happen, but only in the

59:35.340 --> 59:40.380
beginning. And this is like a key element of how this works, right? This weird stuff will happen

59:40.380 --> 59:46.320
in the beginning because that sucks you right in. And once that happens, you cannot deny the evidence

59:46.320 --> 59:51.600
of your senses. There's nobody playing a hoax in that room because it's just your family. They

59:51.600 --> 59:56.480
don't have, believe me, the wherewithal to carry on a hoax like that. It was a little too, you know,

59:56.520 --> 01:00:06.380
elaborate. And that happens. And what happened after that was members of my family became sort

01:00:06.380 --> 01:00:12.640
of entranced with this process to the point where the phenomena never really mattered much anymore.

01:00:12.640 --> 01:00:17.620
It was the contact with spirits. It was a contact with the other side. That became an

01:00:17.620 --> 01:00:22.920
overriding thing. And that drained me completely. That was completely something that really bothered

01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:27.520
me a great deal because it was going nowhere. It was nonsense. At one point we were told there

01:00:27.520 --> 01:00:34.740
was going to be an aboriginal uprising in Australia outside of Perth. It was very specific. And we

01:00:34.740 --> 01:00:39.040
thought, oh my God, this is going to happen. People are going to die. So my mother and I...

01:00:39.040 --> 01:00:41.660
You were told by the spirits. By the spirits. In detail.

