03:05:20.320 --> 03:05:25.940
went on. I broke up with them after this. I didn't want to be associated with them. I didn't know what

03:05:25.940 --> 03:05:32.560
was going on because they kept having these parties where there were, you know, TV types were there or

03:05:32.560 --> 03:05:39.720
Broadway types were there. Not the stuff you're hearing about these days of the Hollywood, you know,

03:05:39.900 --> 03:05:44.240
satanic stuff that's always, you know, on the internet for some reason. It was nothing like that.

03:05:44.260 --> 03:05:47.660
But it was just people attending these parties. But they were making connections. These are people

03:05:47.660 --> 03:05:51.700
disconnecting with each other. And they might be in business. They might be in government. They might be

03:05:51.700 --> 03:05:57.620
in Hollywood. These connections are made. So that was fine. That's what I knew, you know. And I was

03:05:57.620 --> 03:06:02.540
uncomfortable with my position in all of this. I didn't feel that secure. So I left, right?

03:06:03.300 --> 03:06:08.160
As soon as I left the church, I got a notice from Selective Service that I was being drafted.

03:06:10.480 --> 03:06:16.040
So I made a phone call. And after I made the phone call, they dropped that. And they said,

03:06:16.080 --> 03:06:21.080
no, you're okay. I just kind of threatened to talk about what I knew. And they said, no, forget it.

03:06:21.080 --> 03:06:28.180
You're still good. Oh, wow. So then a little bit after that, what happens is I find out that the

03:06:28.180 --> 03:06:32.360
church that I had left, I get a phone call from them, from my partner, from my friend. And he comes

03:06:32.360 --> 03:06:37.900
and says, listen, I need you. If you could just come back for a short time. Something weird is

03:06:37.900 --> 03:06:42.320
going on here. And I think you're the person to look into it. I said, thanks. And it turns out he

03:06:42.320 --> 03:06:48.060
had these monks working for him. Monks, people that I didn't know, people that had come to him from

03:06:48.060 --> 03:06:57.540
some other church. They always do. They cross-fertilize that way. And they specialize in rare books. And he

03:06:57.540 --> 03:07:01.820
thinks they're stealing them because they give him all these great books. And he was still interested

03:07:01.820 --> 03:07:06.720
in occult things as well. So he got these beautiful occult volumes from like the 16th century, 17th

03:07:06.720 --> 03:07:12.200
century, priceless looking things, right? I'm staring at this stuff. He's got a shelf full. And he says,

03:07:12.200 --> 03:07:16.280
these guys are acquiring them. He says, but I have doubts about these guys. I don't know if they're

03:07:16.280 --> 03:07:22.740
legitimately getting these or not. I'm afraid that he's going to expose me to some problems.

03:07:22.860 --> 03:07:28.040
So could you go and spy on them? They've never seen you. They don't know what you look like. Never

03:07:28.040 --> 03:07:32.400
heard of you. Just go there, you know, and say like you're in the book business and you want to see

03:07:32.400 --> 03:07:38.340
what's up. So I did that, right? So I said, yeah, sounds good. So I went to visit them at their

03:07:38.340 --> 03:07:45.040
location, which was, they had a chapel and it was located above a strip club in Jamaica, Queens.

03:07:46.040 --> 03:07:51.060
And upstairs they had, you know, a sort of makeshift chapel, like a little altar in the front

03:07:51.060 --> 03:07:57.880
because they were posing as priests, as monks. And, but in the back room, they had all these,

03:07:57.980 --> 03:08:04.480
this machinery for taking care of the rare books. What they would do is they would steam out any

03:08:04.480 --> 03:08:09.280
library impressions. And if there was ink involved, they had ink eradication equipment

03:08:09.280 --> 03:08:14.080
that wouldn't leave any marks on the books. And then they would tear out the maps and sell

03:08:14.080 --> 03:08:17.440
them separately. Sometimes they would get more money for the map than they would for the book.

03:08:18.700 --> 03:08:25.920
And this to me was anathema. I'm a book lover from day one. So you don't do this to books,

03:08:25.980 --> 03:08:30.620
right? You don't strip, I don't write in my books even, right? So these guys are just,

03:08:30.620 --> 03:08:36.260
you know, ripping off books left and right. So I realized that's what's going on. And, you know,

03:08:36.600 --> 03:08:40.600
after one or two visits with them and everything else, getting acquainted with them, I went back to

03:08:40.600 --> 03:08:46.420
my friend and said, you know, this is, this is what's happening. So then he freaked out that this

03:08:46.420 --> 03:08:54.180
was going to be a big problem for him. So he had all of these priceless books in his possession and he

03:08:54.180 --> 03:09:01.100
destroyed them. He burned them. Whoa. So that he wouldn't get caught. But in the process,

03:09:02.000 --> 03:09:05.740
I snagged one or two things that I thought should be saved from the fire that I would take

03:09:05.740 --> 03:09:09.660
responsibility for. I don't know where he got them. If he got them from these monks, he got them from

03:09:09.660 --> 03:09:14.920
somebody else. But a box of a manuscript, right? Which looked cool to me. And I said, this looks

03:09:14.920 --> 03:09:22.140
pretty cool. I'm going to keep this and see what I can do with it. And so then I brought it to a

03:09:22.140 --> 03:09:27.080
friend of mine who ran an occult bookstore in Brooklyn Heights, the warlock shop, a guy called

03:09:27.080 --> 03:09:34.060
Herman Slater. And I bring the box over to him and he says, oh, this looks great. You know, what is

03:09:34.060 --> 03:09:39.420
it? And I show him the page on the front. It's like a lot of writing, but there's a heavy writing

03:09:39.420 --> 03:09:46.560
in Greek letters in the front. And in my basic rusty Greek, which I only know the Greek alphabet because

03:09:46.560 --> 03:09:51.480
I studied the Russian, the Kyrillic alphabet. I said, this looks like it says nekronomikon.

03:09:52.320 --> 03:09:58.740
And Herman Slater has a heart attack on the spot. He says, no, no, no, no, no, you can't be serious.

03:09:59.480 --> 03:10:05.900
And I said, I don't know. Am I serious about what? I never read occult fiction. You know, so Lovecraft

03:10:05.900 --> 03:10:11.660
meant nothing to me. You know, it's a word that was in the background somewhere, but I never read

03:10:11.660 --> 03:10:16.580
any short stories by Lovecraft. It was not my thing. You know, I gravitated more towards nonfiction

03:10:16.580 --> 03:10:22.720
for magic and occult stuff. I wanted the nonfiction or the closest I came were the Dennis Wheatley

03:10:22.720 --> 03:10:27.020
novels, three novels that he wrote on occultism because they talked about Crowley and they

03:10:27.020 --> 03:10:30.680
talked about Thlema and stuff like that from like another perspective. So I thought that

03:10:30.680 --> 03:10:36.280
was cool. And I just, I read those. But that was it, you know? So now he said, no, you have

03:10:36.280 --> 03:10:40.080
to translate this. You have to see what this is because this looks cool. This, you know, find

03:10:40.080 --> 03:10:47.300
somebody and do it. So that's sort of this whole, um, odyssey of figuring out what this

03:10:47.300 --> 03:10:54.040
book is. You know, is it something that Lovecraft talked about? Is it just a name? You know, it

03:10:54.040 --> 03:10:58.020
has no relationship at all to Lovecraft. I had to learn about Lovecraft. I knew nothing

03:10:58.020 --> 03:11:02.340
about it. So I had to learn about it. And I talked to my friend at the church guy who

03:11:02.340 --> 03:11:06.180
was burning all the books and he didn't have a clue. He didn't want to know at this point

03:11:06.180 --> 03:11:09.940
because now these guys are getting arrested and they were arrested for committing the

03:11:09.940 --> 03:11:15.540
largest rare book theft in America's history. Turns out they had stolen hundreds if not

03:11:15.540 --> 03:11:19.960
thousands of books and sold them all over the place, coast to coast. And in Canada and

03:11:19.960 --> 03:11:24.860
Mexico as well, the Mounties were brought in as part of the investigation. So this was

03:11:24.860 --> 03:11:28.340
a major operation that they were running. Where they, what they did with the money, I don't

03:11:28.340 --> 03:11:33.560
know, but they did get sent to prison. They served time for it, uh, in federal facilities.

03:11:33.560 --> 03:11:39.180
So, you know, my friend was wise to stay, get as far away from it as possible. But still,

03:11:39.260 --> 03:11:42.940
I mean, he was the church they belonged to at the time. They were officially part of his

03:11:42.940 --> 03:11:48.560
operation. So that was, it led to a lot of paranoia on my part, on his part, on the part

03:11:48.560 --> 03:11:54.900
of everybody involved in this thing. But eventually by 1975, October 12th, as it turned

03:11:54.900 --> 03:11:59.620
out, it was just serendipitous. All of the translation work had been done, had been compiled

03:11:59.620 --> 03:12:04.460
basically that we knew what was in the book. And that was the date that we said, okay, we're

03:12:04.460 --> 03:12:10.620
finished. This is it. Now what do we do with it? Right? So Herman Slater held onto it for

03:12:10.620 --> 03:12:16.400
a while. Um, the only copy of it and the only translation was his. Okay, you do something

03:12:16.400 --> 03:12:23.480
with this. Right? So then, um, thereby leads another tale because then a guy called Larry

03:12:23.480 --> 03:12:28.860
Barnes walks into our lives. And Larry Barnes was one of the most incredible people I've

03:12:28.860 --> 03:12:37.360
met in my life, a very strange guy, but strange in a nice way. He, um, he walks into the store

03:12:37.360 --> 03:12:41.220
and he looks at all the weird stuff that's hanging. There's, there's skulls and there's,

03:12:41.260 --> 03:12:45.320
you know, there's daggers and there's all these books and there's herbs. There's whole bunches

03:12:45.320 --> 03:12:49.420
of herbs and roots and stuff. And he goes over to Herman Slater and he says, um, you wouldn't

03:12:49.420 --> 03:12:54.040
happen to have a copy of the Necronomicon in here, would you? And Herman Slater very victoriously

03:12:54.040 --> 03:12:59.320
pulls it from underneath the counter, right? He says, here it is. And so Larry Barnes went

03:12:59.320 --> 03:13:04.360
absolutely nuts because he was a total cartoon freak and a Lovecraft freak and everything, uh,

03:13:04.360 --> 03:13:09.840
from the art side, not from the occult side, just from the, you know, the vibe side. So he was just

03:13:09.840 --> 03:13:16.600
totally into this like big time. So he then wanted to publish the book actually. Uh, believe it or

03:13:16.600 --> 03:13:20.440
not, nobody wanted to publish it. Nobody was that interested in it at the time, but Larry

03:13:20.440 --> 03:13:25.520
Barnes came up with it and says, oh my God, we can do something with this. So he, uh, he got me

03:13:25.520 --> 03:13:31.160
involved. He got, um, a number of people involved, people who had been belonged to various occult societies

03:13:31.160 --> 03:13:36.520
and stuff who had the connections to do some of the, the, uh, the typesetting. In those days,

03:13:36.600 --> 03:13:42.620
there were no computers per se. So making a book was much more laborious than it is now. Uh, you had

03:13:42.620 --> 03:13:46.580
to set type and you had to redraw a lot of the art. You couldn't just copy it. It had

03:13:46.580 --> 03:13:50.380
to be done a certain way. So it was a lot of fussy stuff that was involved. So it took

03:13:50.380 --> 03:13:57.980
a while. So I finally, by 1977, uh, by December of 77, there was a completed actual book for

03:13:57.980 --> 03:14:04.940
sale. But to get to your initial question, which has been like a half an hour ago, um,

03:14:04.940 --> 03:14:08.780
what does it have to do with the strategic air command? What happened was...

03:14:08.780 --> 03:14:10.820
Well, what, and what's in the Necronomicon?

03:14:10.820 --> 03:14:15.740
John. Oh, okay. Well, if you're a Lovecraft person, you have some ideas as to what must

03:14:15.740 --> 03:14:22.000
be in it. It's kind of like that. It's a grimoire. It's a, it's a book, um, that pretends

03:14:22.000 --> 03:14:27.680
to be a pre-Islamic or if not anti-Islamic, it's not anti-Islamic because there's nothing

03:14:27.680 --> 03:14:33.660
anti-Islamic in it. But I would say pre-Islamic, a book of casting spells of, of, of conjuring

03:14:33.660 --> 03:14:39.500
spirits. Uh, and there's even a kind of, of, of abbreviated version of the creation

03:14:39.500 --> 03:14:44.680
epic, the Sumerian creation epic in it. There's Sumerian words in it, Sumerian deities, and

03:14:44.680 --> 03:14:50.080
then there's some Babylonian and Akkadian. It's kind of mixed. Um, it seems to be a book

03:14:50.080 --> 03:14:57.900
of, you know, that a sorcerer might've used, uh, in the Middle East, probably Iraq, uh, before

03:14:57.900 --> 03:15:02.160
the advent of Islam or before Islam really took over and basically destroyed a lot of that

03:15:02.160 --> 03:15:07.460
material. So you found the only copy of it essentially. Essentially. Yeah. Wow. Handwritten.

03:15:07.860 --> 03:15:13.780
Right. That's crazy. Yeah. That's what it is. And that's, and what's, but we didn't know

03:15:13.780 --> 03:15:17.840
what it was. What's the Lovecraft writes about it or? Well, Lovecraft writes that it's a dangerous

03:15:17.840 --> 03:15:22.580
book that even possessing it means you're, you're summoning demons and spirits and stuff. And it's

03:15:22.580 --> 03:15:27.760
a gateway, a portal to other dimensions. And you found it. And it, and what's, I don't know

03:15:27.760 --> 03:15:31.640
if it's it. I mean, Lovecraft scholars will say, no, that's not it. It's not, it's not

03:15:31.640 --> 03:15:35.380
Lovecraftian enough. Okay. I mean, if it was going to be a hoax, do a better hoax is

03:15:35.380 --> 03:15:40.740
their, their response. Right. But it might be it. It might, it's a book with the same

03:15:40.740 --> 03:15:48.100
name. Okay. Does it, well, does it, if you do like a, an unbiased, you know, historiographic

03:15:48.100 --> 03:15:53.800
kind of analysis on it, does it sort of comport with, you know, uh, materials at that time,

03:15:53.860 --> 03:15:59.980
written materials or. I think the more we know now. Yeah. The closer it becomes to a real

03:15:59.980 --> 03:16:04.940
thing. When they first came out, people rose a lot of objections to it. And I think on

03:16:04.940 --> 03:16:09.600
pretty standard sound grounds, phonetic grounds, for instance, things like that, where it couldn't

03:16:09.600 --> 03:16:13.600
have meant, it couldn't have been this, it could not have been that. Uh, we make the point

03:16:13.600 --> 03:16:21.120
in the book that, uh, Lovecraft's famous arch weird connector between humans and the, the

03:16:21.120 --> 03:16:28.500
elder gods or the ancient ones is Cthulhu. And it's spelled C-T-H-U-L-H-U. Right. No one

03:16:28.500 --> 03:16:31.900
knows how it's really pronounced. It's like supposed to be a garbling in the throat sound.

03:16:31.980 --> 03:16:37.440
Like it's not, it's a non-human alphabet, right? A non-human name. But we're looking

03:16:37.440 --> 03:16:42.940
at it and came up with the idea. We talked to a scholar of Sumeriology. You have to have

03:16:42.940 --> 03:16:48.360
somebody who knows Sumerian. And he said, Cthulhu. I mean, that's a Sumerian form. It means

03:16:48.360 --> 03:16:53.660
a person from the underworld. Cthulhu is the underworld. And Lu means person. It means a human

03:16:53.660 --> 03:16:58.680
being or a man. So it's the man from the underworld. This Cthulhu that they're talking

03:16:58.680 --> 03:17:04.340
about in the book is the man from the underworld. And then, so that sent us off on other wild

03:17:04.340 --> 03:17:09.360
goose chases. Like, Kutu is the underworld. And we found out there is a place. It's, I mean,

03:17:09.380 --> 03:17:14.760
the Sumeriologists would know. It was called Kuta or Kutu in Sumerian or Babylonian. And it

03:17:14.760 --> 03:17:20.480
was a place that was supposed to be the entrance to the underworld. It exists today, today in Iraq.

03:17:20.480 --> 03:17:27.960
It's south of Baghdad, south east of Baghdad. And it's the place where Abraham is said to be

03:17:27.960 --> 03:17:33.360
buried. Tell Ibrahim is there. And if you look at pictures of it now, it's just a big empty

03:17:33.360 --> 03:17:37.460
wasteland. Nothing is built there. But that's supposed to be the entrance to the underworld.

03:17:39.180 --> 03:17:39.900
So fascinating.

03:17:40.080 --> 03:17:42.120
So things started to make sense later.

03:17:42.280 --> 03:17:42.600
Yeah.

03:17:42.760 --> 03:17:47.420
Right? And they found an Arabic rendering in the Quran of a being called Al-Khadul,

03:17:47.420 --> 03:17:55.340
which is supposed to be a kind of quality of anti-something. It's like an adversary

03:17:55.340 --> 03:18:01.120
name. Right? So there's like, things started to make sense that didn't make sense back in 1975.

03:18:01.640 --> 03:18:04.740
But with the passage of time and, you know, sober looking back at it,

03:18:05.380 --> 03:18:09.880
things kind of start connecting more than they used to. But from an unbiased perspective,

03:18:09.880 --> 03:18:14.300
I can't be unbiased. I was involved with it since like the beginning. But from my unbiased

03:18:14.300 --> 03:18:21.220
perspective, it's a book with the same name. And it's quite possible that somebody knew about it.

03:18:21.520 --> 03:18:28.080
Lovecraft heard the name, you know, and crafted his idea of what the Necronomicon should be based

03:18:28.080 --> 03:18:33.080
on that, that he just simply heard the name and that the name was around. Because there isn't a lot

03:18:33.080 --> 03:18:38.620
in there that says, that screams Lovecraft. But there are pieces that do, you know?

03:18:38.620 --> 03:18:45.620
And real quick, before we get into the government's interest in this topic, which, you know,

03:18:45.640 --> 03:18:50.960
is mind-blowing that the government and Strategic Air Command might be interested in a book about

03:18:50.960 --> 03:18:58.220
the dead that references ancient, you know, Sumerian myth and stuff. I mean, that's fascinating.

03:18:58.760 --> 03:19:05.280
But truly, your life does resemble Johnny Depp's character in The Ninth Gate,

03:19:05.280 --> 03:19:12.400
this book collector's on this mission to find these like three, like devil books or whatever.

03:19:12.860 --> 03:19:16.560
And so I didn't realize this before doing this interview until Lincoln actually brought it up.

03:19:16.580 --> 03:19:21.420
But you are the inspiration for Johnny Depp's character in the ninth, in Roman Polanski's

03:19:21.420 --> 03:19:26.100
famous movie, The Ninth Gate, which is also, I think, Jacques Vallée's favorite movie.

03:19:26.680 --> 03:19:27.680
I didn't know that.

03:19:27.680 --> 03:19:28.120
Oh, yeah.

03:19:28.540 --> 03:19:32.800
Oh, boy. Okay. I'm in deep trouble now. Now Jacques's going to call me up and say,

03:19:32.800 --> 03:19:40.880
it was you. No. Okay. This is the thing. We have to pull back a little bit. The story is

03:19:40.880 --> 03:19:47.280
not based on me at all. The story was a Spanish novel, very well-known Spanish novel. So the

03:19:47.280 --> 03:19:52.840
story has nothing to do with me. The character of Johnny Depp, however, from what I've been told

03:19:52.840 --> 03:19:57.900
by the people who worked on the Polanski film when they were in New York, see, Polanski can't come to

03:19:57.900 --> 03:20:05.880
the States for reasons I think we all know. He was accused of sexual abuse of a minor. So he is now

03:20:05.980 --> 03:20:11.280
in France virtually forever. So he doesn't come to the United States. He's filmed, he's made movies

03:20:11.280 --> 03:20:17.240
in the United States, but he hasn't come himself. So he has scouts that do the, you know, the B-roll

03:20:17.240 --> 03:20:22.540
stuff and they look for the, you know, location shots and stuff like that. And some of the movie

03:20:22.540 --> 03:20:27.260
takes place in New York. So there were people in New York working for Polanski. And they came

03:20:27.260 --> 03:20:33.940
across this story. They came across the story of myself and the book and all of this. And they got

03:20:33.940 --> 03:20:40.040
the physical description down. Right. So I was even thinner then than I am now. I was like maybe 125.

03:20:41.620 --> 03:20:45.940
I always wore suits. That's a whole other story, but I always wore suits and tie constantly.

03:20:45.940 --> 03:20:52.720
I wore a black sort of trench coat, raincoat kind of thing. I had a beard, obviously. I always had a

03:20:52.720 --> 03:20:57.960
shoulder bag, glasses, the whole nine yards. I mean, it's the Johnny Depp character, dark clothing,

03:20:58.080 --> 03:21:02.780
the whole thing. And the book business guy, I was always in and out of bookstores, right,

03:21:02.840 --> 03:21:09.000
in that outfit. And I was involved with Weiser's bookstore, which in New York City was the famous

03:21:09.000 --> 03:21:12.400
occult bookstore with a pedigree going back a long time.

03:21:12.400 --> 03:21:19.580
And you came upon maybe the occult book, which is the Necronomicon, which is like the most

03:21:19.580 --> 03:21:23.600
forbidden book that you're not supposed to possess, which ends up kind of being true for

03:21:23.600 --> 03:21:27.600
Johnny Depp and his character as well, where you're really not supposed to possess all three books.

03:21:27.680 --> 03:21:32.300
You see, but they had the story already. So I fit, unbeknownst to me, because I hadn't read the

03:21:32.300 --> 03:21:38.600
novel at that time, right? But I fit the whole thing. It was as though it was scripted. So the people

03:21:38.600 --> 03:21:44.400
around Depp are saying, this actually happened. This story actually happened to this guy, you

03:21:44.400 --> 03:21:47.920
know, and we have all this information about him and we talk to people who knew him and stuff.

03:21:48.360 --> 03:21:52.600
And so that kind of got into the film. From what I understand, I had forgotten all about this to

03:21:52.600 --> 03:21:58.140
tell you the truth until a few months ago, I was talking to a guy who makes a videographer.

03:21:59.000 --> 03:22:04.220
Actually, I think he's based in Florida as well. And he came down to meet me just a couple of months

03:22:04.220 --> 03:22:10.260
ago. And he says, do you remember that thing about Johnny Depp and the Ninth Gate? And I said,

03:22:10.280 --> 03:22:13.600
oh my God, I'd forgotten all about that. And he told me the story again. So it's been around.

03:22:14.180 --> 03:22:16.960
The story has been around. I don't know who's promulgated it, but it's been around.

03:22:17.480 --> 03:22:23.840
So yeah, that's kind of weird. But imagine me, but, you know, like 40 years ago. That's pretty

03:22:23.840 --> 03:22:24.580
much how I looked.

03:22:24.980 --> 03:22:29.860
So wild. So if I'm strategic air command, why do I care at all?

03:22:30.120 --> 03:22:31.200
Well, this is how that happened.

03:22:31.200 --> 03:22:34.120
Yeah. We're going to announce the book now.

03:22:36.800 --> 03:22:40.760
Larry Barnes is financing the publication of this book, and it's costing some money

